1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,544
Three days from now,

2
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:05,213
<i>a high-level conference</i>
<i>will take place</i>

3
00:00:05,296 --> 00:00:07,465
<i>for the Japanese</i>
<i>investment deal.</i>

4
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:12,387
<i>Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha</i>
<i>will be here today</i>

5
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:17,684
<i>to oversee Datu Rahman</i>
<i>Abubakar's formal release.</i>

6
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:21,855
[Mustapha] <i>We're just making them</i>
<i>believe that their plans are sailing.</i>

7
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:23,273
[Jalil]
<i>What do you mean, sir?</i>

8
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:27,193
<i>[Mustapha] Only General Carillo is</i>
<i>capable of doing all of that.</i>

9
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:29,696
<i>He was able to gain</i>
<i>the trust of the president.</i>

10
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:33,199
<i>That's why we can't carelessly</i>
<i>throw accusations at him.</i>

11
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,368
We only have one chance.

12
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:38,371
And when we strike,
it should be bullseye.

13
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:42,208
We need to take down
General Carillo.

14
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,419
[Marcus] <i>Whatever you see on the news</i>
<i>isn't true, Ma.</i>

15
00:00:44,502 --> 00:00:47,964
If they're able to create
a spectacle as huge as this,

16
00:00:48,047 --> 00:00:51,301
<i>it means they are planning</i>
<i>something far worse.</i>

17
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:53,386
<i>[Jamilah]</i>
<i>We can go back to the island.</i>

18
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:54,721
<i>[Jalil]</i>
<i>My mission will not be over</i>

19
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:59,100
until I get real justice
for our people.

20
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,519
<i>I'm keeping that promise</i>
<i>no matter what happens.</i>

21
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:09,903
[theme music playing]

22
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:20,580
[tense music playing]

23
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:26,336
General Villanueva is requiring
strict police visibility

24
00:01:26,419 --> 00:01:30,381
around NLEA and SID premises.

25
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:32,717
That includes Task Force Alpha.

26
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:35,261
All of this is in preparation

27
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:38,139
for the arrival of
the Japanese investors.

28
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:42,477
And while we're waiting
for our next mission,

29
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:46,439
we will patrol the city
to prevent any crime.

30
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:49,400
We must show the people

31
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:54,072
that the police and Task Force
Alpha are on their side.

32
00:01:54,155 --> 00:01:55,740
Sir, whose idea was this?

33
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:57,659
General Carillo's.

34
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:03,915
Everyone is looking forward
to tomorrow.

35
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:07,544
I want all of you to be
at the top of your game

36
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:10,004
when the Japanese investors arrive.

37
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,047
Understood?

38
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,507
- Sir, yes, sir!
- Sir, yes, sir!

39
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,385
Good. Carry on.

40
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,514
Sir.

41
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:23,560
Alright, team.
You heard Director Azuelo.

42
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:25,436
Be at the top of
your game tomorrow.

43
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:30,024
In order to be more efficient,
we will work in pairs.

44
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,902
Sabdani, you're with me.

45
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,028
Roger.

46
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,948
- [Lara] Alright, Domingo--
- [Marcus] Domingo.

47
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,076
Pair up with Suarez.

48
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,161
Copy, sir.

49
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:44,414
I'll partner up with Agent Angeles.

50
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:47,792
- [Jalil] That okay?
- Wait, what?

51
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:53,131
I'm fine with whoever
you pair me up with.

52
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,216
I'm game, sir.

53
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:59,721
Sean, buddy! Looks like
it's you and me again.

54
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,265
[taps back]

55
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:07,270
[tense music continues]

56
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,362
- [Zubina] That's carabao meat.
- [Idah] Wow.

57
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:18,156
[Ibrahim] It's really good.

58
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:19,574
- [Idah] I'll have one serving.
- [Zubina] Give her more.

59
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:20,992
[Malik] Oh? What's this?

60
00:03:21,075 --> 00:03:23,328
- [Ibrahim] Get some more.
- [Zubina] Sure thing.

61
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:24,829
[Idah] Give me extra pieces.

62
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:27,081
- [Idah] Want some dessert?
- [in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

63
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,166
Peace be with you.

64
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:30,084
[Zubina] How about this one?
You want this one?

65
00:03:30,168 --> 00:03:32,503
[Malik] The chicken looks good too.

66
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:33,796
[Zubina] Yeah, try the chicken too.

67
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,174
- Good morning, Datu Rahman!
- Peace be upon you.

68
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:37,759
Peace be upon you, Datu Rahman.

69
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:39,636
- You too.
- Datu Rahman! Good morning!

70
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,930
- Let's eat! Come on.
- Oh.

71
00:03:42,013 --> 00:03:43,640
Thank you, auntie.

72
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:46,976
Datu Rahman, please try my specialty.

73
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,478
<i>Tiyula itum</i>

74
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:49,896
- You'll love it.
- [in Tausug] Thank you.

75
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:51,856
- thank you, ibrahim.
- [Idah] Set it on the table.

76
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,566
- [Jamilah] Father!
- [Idah] Perfect.

77
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:54,943
[Datu Rahman] Dear.

78
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:56,736
Mm!

79
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:58,613
I'm off to work, Father.

80
00:03:58,696 --> 00:04:02,283
I can't wait to go straight home
after my shift

81
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,827
knowing you're here.

82
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:06,955
- [Jamilah chuckles]
- Be careful, okay?

83
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,623
Don't worry, Rahman.

84
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:10,667
We'll give Jamilah a ride.

85
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:15,046
Thank you very much, Omar,
for taking care of my daughter.

86
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,840
[chuckles] Bye, father.

87
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:18,967
- I have to go.
- Okay.

88
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,385
- Bye!
- Take care.

89
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:22,845
- Bye!
- Enjoy your breakfast.

90
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:26,557
Thank you. Bye!
We'll take care of things here.

91
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:28,851
Grab a seat, Datu Rahman.
Let's eat!

92
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:31,396
- Go ahead and eat first.
- I'm sure you'll love these.

93
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:33,273
- I'll have breakfast later.
- They're best served hot!

94
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:36,192
- That's right!
- Get the serving spoon.

95
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:38,236
[Zubina] Wow!

96
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:42,907
[poignant music playing]

97
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,600
[music fades]

98
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:10,977
[traffic noise]

99
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:14,147
POLICE

100
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:18,067
Why did you make me
your partner, huh?

101
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,069
To annoy me?
Because it's working.

102
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:21,904
Is there a problem, Agent Angeles?

103
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,574
Let's just split up.
This buddy system isn't working.

104
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,659
I can manage.
I don't need your help.

105
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,786
Is it me you hate?

106
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:32,290
Or is it the thought of
seeking help from others

107
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:34,208
and appearing weak?

108
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:37,420
[tense music playing]

109
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,256
Agent Angeles, I know you
are strong and tough.

110
00:05:40,339 --> 00:05:42,425
But no one can
stay strong at all times.

111
00:05:42,508 --> 00:05:45,011
There will come a time
when you will feel weak.

112
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:47,805
And that's okay because
that's just how humans are.

113
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:49,599
We get tired sometimes.

114
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:51,768
But remember…

115
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:54,270
Feeling weak isn't something
to be ashamed of.

116
00:05:54,353 --> 00:06:00,026
[music turns pensive]

117
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:07,158
Don't pretend that you know me
because you don't,

118
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:08,826
so leave me alone.

119
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:13,664
[pensive music continues]

120
00:06:25,384 --> 00:06:27,428
Brother, I noticed something.

121
00:06:29,013 --> 00:06:30,056
What is it?

122
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,559
It seems Jamilah's got you smitten.

123
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:36,687
- [Marcus chuckles]
- [soft music playing]

124
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:38,231
Why bring it up all of a sudden?

125
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:41,109
Is that a bad thing?

126
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:45,696
You can't be with Jamilah.

127
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,323
You don't have a chance.

128
00:06:50,868 --> 00:06:52,537
How are you so sure?

129
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:55,289
Well, under Islamic Law,

130
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:58,459
a Muslim woman cannot marry
a non-Muslim man.

131
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,259
You think it's impossible?

132
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,720
Converting is always an option.

133
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:16,060
If a man genuinely wants to be
with a Muslim woman

134
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,854
for the rest of his life,

135
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:21,107
he must respect, learn about,

136
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:23,693
and accept the Muslim way of life.

137
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:28,573
That's how much we respect
our religion.

138
00:07:30,741 --> 00:07:32,201
I know that, buddy.

139
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:36,747
Is converting to Islam difficult?

140
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:37,999
[chuckles]

141
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:42,086
[soft music continues]

142
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:53,931
[unsettling music playing]

143
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:05,151
[music becomes morose]

144
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:27,131
[morose music continues]

145
00:08:33,804 --> 00:08:39,060
- [explosion]
- [people screaming]

146
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:46,275
Didn't I tell you not to follow me?

147
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,695
[morose music playing]

148
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:08,256
[music fades]

149
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:13,052
[pensive music playing]

150
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:34,323
[pensive music continues]

151
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:04,770
[pensive music continues]

152
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,035
What's this, huh?

153
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:22,496
Explain this.

154
00:10:23,247 --> 00:10:26,459
I saw you looking at it
at the toy shop earlier.

155
00:10:27,335 --> 00:10:29,295
And then you smiled.

156
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:32,590
That was the first time
I saw you smile.

157
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:35,635
[gentle music playing]

158
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:39,096
It seemed special to you so I bought it.

159
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,142
So, why are you doing this?

160
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:48,564
Do we need to have a reason
to show kindness?

161
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,902
I just wanted to make you smile.

162
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:59,200
[gentle music continues]

163
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,790
What's with the doll
that made you smile?

164
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:13,339
[gentle music continues]

165
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:40,574
[gentle music continues]

166
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:53,671
[Jalil] <i>I hope you're not</i>
<i>an accomplice, Lara.</i>

167
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:56,173
<i>I don't want you to get</i>
<i>dragged into this.</i>

168
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,473
- [tense music playing]
- [guns clacking]

169
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:07,601
Let's rock and roll!

170
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,942
General Carillo personally requested

171
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:17,570
that we keep an eye
on the investors.

172
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,489
What do you think is his plan?

173
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:22,116
I don't know.

174
00:12:22,199 --> 00:12:23,742
But it's all over the news

175
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:26,996
that he's the consultant
and overseer of the summit.

176
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,206
Would he ruin his reputation?

177
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,626
We need to be vigilant.

178
00:12:33,502 --> 00:12:35,921
I can sense that he's up to something.

179
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:47,683
[unsettling music playing]

180
00:13:07,953 --> 00:13:10,331
[humming]

181
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:13,292
[Manuel breathing deeply]

182
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:14,627
- General.
- Hmm?

183
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,545
- The car is ready.
- Mm-hmm.

184
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:20,382
[unsettling music playing]

185
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:35,856
- Raquel…
- Hmm?

186
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:41,570
This is going to be
the best day of my life!

187
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:42,780
[chuckles]

188
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:52,831
[unsettling music continues]

189
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:12,810
[music fades]

190
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:16,397
[keyboard clacking]

191
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:20,067
Ma'am, a package came
for you earlier.

192
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,528
- Is this it?
- Yes, that one.

193
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:24,446
[ominous music playing]

194
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:33,330
[plastic rustling]

195
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:52,099
[ominous music swells]

196
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:56,562
Ma'am, are you okay?

197
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,900
- Yeah. Get back at work.
- Copy that, ma'am.

198
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,444
[keyboard clacking]

199
00:15:03,527 --> 00:15:09,325
[ominous music continues]

200
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:18,250
[pensive music playing]

201
00:15:21,378 --> 00:15:27,134
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

202
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:43,108
[engine humming]

203
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:49,281
["Maninindigan" continues]

204
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,961
Make sure the perimeter
is secure, okay?

205
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:03,587
Give it a thorough check later.

206
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,215
- [man]Yes, sir.
- You all know your assignments.

207
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:08,008
They'll be arriving any minute now.

208
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,551
Dismissed.

209
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:12,304
["Maninindigan" continues]

210
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:35,202
["Maninindigan" continues]

211
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:54,680
[tires screech]

212
00:16:58,517 --> 00:16:59,935
[car doors close]

213
00:17:06,483 --> 00:17:11,530
["Maninindigan" continues]

214
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:32,468
["Maninindigan" continues]

215
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:43,854
[man] [speaking in Japanese]
Hello to the host!

216
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:45,147
[organizer]
[speaking in Japanese] Hello.

217
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,399
Welcome to the Philippines, gentlemen.

218
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:52,196
By the way, this is
Retired General Manuel Carillo.

219
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:56,241
And he is in charge of
your security operations today.

220
00:17:57,534 --> 00:17:59,078
[speaking in Japanese] Hello.

221
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:00,913
I'm honored to meet you.

222
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:03,207
[speaking in Japanese]
Thank you so much for having us.

223
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,336
We are very pleased to be here
for this summit.

224
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:08,962
Good.

225
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:14,384
This is our elite team,
Task Force Alpha.

226
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:18,430
[speaking in Japanese]
They'll keep you safe.

227
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:22,184
They will personally be in charge

228
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:26,438
of your security and protection
for the whole day.

229
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:27,940
[speaking in Japanese] Thank you.

230
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:32,861
- ["Maninindigan" continues]
- [camera shutters clicking]

231
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:55,592
["Maninindigan" continues]

232
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:08,522
[music becomes eerie]

233
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:20,617
What scheme are you
cooking up now, General Carillo?

234
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:22,661
[uneasy music playing]

235
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,174
[music fades]

236
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:38,552
Okay, everyone! As you can see,

237
00:19:38,635 --> 00:19:42,639
we are now entering
the Tamaraw Eco Park!

238
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:46,810
Yes, the Philippines' exotic and endemic

239
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:50,063
flora and fauna
conservation sanctuary.

240
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:53,275
Yes, spanning hundreds of hectares,

241
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:56,069
this sanctuary is famously known as…

242
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:59,823
the green lung of Metro Manila.

243
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:03,243
Later, I will guide you through
the sanctuary's trail,

244
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:06,288
but for now,
please enjoy the view.

245
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:13,670
[grim music playing]

246
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:33,732
[grim music continues]

247
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,041
[news reporter]
<i>the official summit begins soon</i>

248
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:52,793
<i>for a major investment agreement</i>

249
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:56,004
<i>between Japanese investors</i>
<i>and Filipino businessmen.</i>

250
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:59,049
I still don't know what
General Carillo is planning.

251
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:01,134
Let's keep surveillance on him.

252
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,135
TOURIST

253
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:05,889
Just keep a close watch
on everyone nearby.

254
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:07,516
Definitely, sir.

255
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,226
- Sit down! Move!
- [passengers gasping]

256
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:10,644
Sit down!

257
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:13,605
[passengers shrieking, sobbing]

258
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,023
[Lydia] [speaking in Japanese]
Move it!

259
00:21:15,649 --> 00:21:16,858
[Lydia] [speaking in Japanese]
<i>Hurry up!</i>

260
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:18,986
<i>From this moment on,</i>

261
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:25,242
you people are our hostages!

262
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:28,328
[passengers whimpering, sobbing]

263
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:33,250
Anyone tries anything,
I'll kill you! Understood?!

264
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:37,504
[passengers sobbing in fear]

265
00:21:37,587 --> 00:21:39,006
Got it?!

266
00:21:39,089 --> 00:21:41,425
[sobbing continues]

267
00:21:41,508 --> 00:21:43,593
[whimpering softly]

268
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:47,180
[anxious chattering]
